Description of available methods:
---------------------------------

  gauge( taglist )

    This method initialises the plugin.

    <taglist> is a pointer to a normal taglist.

    The following tags are available:

    - GAUGE_BorderX        : borderheight
    - GAUGE_BorderY        : borderwidth
    - GAUGE_Units          : max. value
    - GAUGE_BorderType     : GTYP_NONE         ; no border
                             GTYP_SINGLE       ; single border
                             GTYP_DOUBLE       ; double border
    - GAUGE_InitState      : inital value (from 0 to GAUGE_Units)
    - GAUGE_FillPen        : color of the bar
    - GAUGE_BackPen        : color behind the bar
    - GAUGE_BorderPen      : color of the border
    - GAUGE_Height         : fixed height
    - GAUGE_Width          : fixed width
    - GAUGE_Border         : GTYP_3D          ; 3D border
                             GTYP_2D          ; flat border
                             GTYP_XEN         ; xen-style border
    - GAUGE_Bar            : GTYP_3D          ; 3D bar
                             GTYP_2D          ; flat bar
                             GTYP_XEN         ; xen-style bar
    - GAUGE_BorderRecessed : (boolean)
    - GAUGE_BarRecessed    : (boolean)
(   - GAUGE_Direction      : not available yet)

-> not all options are available for every bordertype

  set( newstate )

    set the new state of the bar (between 0 and GAUGE_Units)


